result.execSummary:
The defendant Anthony DeBauche was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Anthony DeBauche is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Anthony DeBauche was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant is sentenced to 10 days in the Dane County Jail.  That jail term is stayed one year for completion of 56 hours of community service.
$243 to be paid by the defendant to the Clerk of Courts office within 60 days.  $200 DNA surcharge remitted.
